headline: Is DaVita Attractive After a 21% Drop in 2025 Amid Policy Uncertainty?
summary: If you are wondering whether DaVita at around $118 a share is a bargain or a value trap, you are not alone. This breakdown is designed to help you assess the situation with more confidence. The stock is roughly flat over the last week, down about 1.2% over the past month and about 21% year to date, but still up almost 59% over three years. headline: DaVita Names New Leaders to Accelerate Care Transformation
summary: DaVita, a leading provider of kidney care services, today announced two key additions to its executive leadership team: Stephanie Hendrickson has been named Chief People Officer (CPO) and Steve Phillips will serve as Chief Strategy Officer (CSO), effective immediately. Both leaders bring more than a decade of proven success at DaVita and deep expertise that will help shape the company's next chapter of growth and innovation.
